International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 13 Mar 2019
Source: Odishatv.in [edited]
https://odishatv.in/odisha/elephant-carcasses-in-balasore-trigger-anthrax-fear-357905


Forest officials found on [Tue 12 Mar 2019] [decomposed] carcasses of 2 female elephants in Kuldiha Wildlife Sanctuary in the district. The death of the 2 elephants is suspected to be caused by anthrax. The carcasses were reportedly found within a distance of about 200m in the sanctuary following which the forest department officials informed their higher-ups.

Later, the regional chief conservator of forest (RCCF) and assistant conservator of forest (ACF), Kuldiha reached the spot and sent the carcasses for post-mortem [evaluation]. Preliminary investigations suggest that the elephants were suffering from anthrax, said Laxman Kumar Pradhan, ACF, Kuldiha. "We suspect that the elephants were suffering from anthrax but the actual reason behind the death can be established only after receiving the post-mortem report," said Pradhan.

[byline: Tanima Ray & Pradeep Singh]

