Anthrax - India (15): (OR) elephant, susp

The actual TV report has the carcasses as "decomposed" -- that is, not freshly dead. Transporting these carcasses to the state diagnostic laboratory must have been an interesting experience. But the advantage is that the park site-contamination will be minimal, and burning the parts in the laboratory incinerator is effective though slow. Personally I don't recommend necropsying elephant anthrax carcasses as a blood sample for culturing is usually adequate; accessing an elephant's nasal turbinate bones would be challenging but would be a more reliable sample in the face of decomposition. - Mod.MHJ

